pull_request.title: Fix: Comprehensive Bug Hunt and UX/Accessibility Improvements
pull_request.body:
This commit addresses a wide range of issues identified during a comprehensive QA assessment of the web application. The fixes improve functionality, accessibility, user experience, and visual integrity.

Key changes include:
- **Critical Bug Fixes:**
  - Replaced all broken or non-direct image links with high-quality, functional URLs.
  - Made the "Location" buttons functional by linking them to Google Maps searches.
  - Implemented a placeholder "feature coming soon" alert for the "Add to Itinerary" button to manage user expectations.

- **Accessibility Enhancements:**
  - Made all attraction cards keyboard-focusable and operable via "Enter" or "Space" keys.
  - Implemented robust focus management for the sanctuary view, ensuring focus is correctly trapped and returned upon closing.
  - Added appropriate `role` and `aria-label` attributes to interactive elements.

- **UX and Performance Improvements:**
  - Replaced the misleading "clock" icon with a "plus" icon for the "Add to Itinerary" button.
  - Added a data URI poster to the landing video to prevent 404 errors and improve loading experience.
  - Added comments to `index.html` recommending image optimization for production environments.

These changes result in a more robust, accessible, and user-friendly application.

Summary

- Introduces phased biome transition (Zoom In → Tunnel Journey → Zoom Out) orchestrated via TransitionOrchestrator.
- Disables player input during transitions (InputManager enable/disable + clear pressed keys) to prevent “stuck keys.”
- Refactors project structure into core/managers/systems/transitions; moves AppOne and LandingScreen; adds MeshLoader, MeshPlacementManager, BiomeDataManager, BiomeEnvironmentApplier, CooldownManager.
- Adds FPS counter and disables debug mode by default.
- Adds travel.mov transition asset; removes legacy PlanetTransition and old top-level files.
Breaking changes

- Several files moved; update imports if referencing old paths (AppOne, LandingScreen, BiomeManager, Materials, PlayerMovement).
How to test

- Trigger a biome transition: confirm Zoom In → Tunnel Journey → Zoom Out, input locked during the sequence and re-enabled afterward with no stuck keys.

issue.title: [WIP] The logic for determining test status is incorrect. The condition `i < passed_tests` assumes tests are processed in order and all passing tests come first, but tests can fail individually. This will show incorrect status for tests that actually passed. Consider tracking individual test results in a list or dictionary instead.
issue.body:
Thanks for assigning this issue to me. I'm starting to work on it and will keep this PR's description up to date as I form a plan and make progress.

Original issue description:

> The logic for determining test status is incorrect. The condition `i < passed_tests` assumes tests are processed in order and all passing tests come first, but tests can fail individually. This will show incorrect status for tests that actually passed. Consider tracking individual test results in a list or dictionary instead.
> ```suggestion
>     for (test_name, _), result in zip(tests, test_results):
>         status = "✅ PASS" if result else "❌ FAIL"
> ```
> 
> _Ursprünglich gepostet von @copilot-pull-request-reviewer in https://github.com/Darkness308/CTMM---PDF-in-LaTex/pull/744#discussion_r2280417847_

pull_request.title: Add 4-hour traffic statistics and update custom date translations
pull_request.body:
This PR implements comprehensive enhancements to the V2RaySocks traffic analysis system by adding 4-hour statistics and updating translations as requested in the requirements.

## Changes Made

### 📊 Enhanced Dashboard Statistics

Added 4-hour traffic statistics to both the traffic dashboard and real-time monitor pages:

- **Active Users (4 hours)**: New statistic showing user activity over the past 4 hours, positioned after the 1-hour statistic
- **4-hour Traffic**: New traffic measurement displaying bandwidth usage over the past 4 hours, positioned after the 1-hour traffic

The 4-hour statistics appear in both:
- **Traffic Dashboard** (`traffic_dashboard.php`): Main analytics page
- **Real-time Monitor** (`real_time_monitor.php`): Live monitoring page

### 🌍 Translation Updates

Updated the "Custom Range" translation to "Custom Date" across all supported languages:

- **Chinese Simplified**: `自定义范围` → `自定义日期`
- **English**: `Custom Range` → `Custom Date`  
- **Chinese Traditional**: `自訂範圍` → `自定義日期`

### ⚙️ Backend Implementation

Enhanced the backend statistics calculation in `Monitor_DB.php`:

```php
// Added 4-hour active users calculation
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) as active_users FROM user_usage WHERE t >= :time_4hour');
$stmt->execute([':time_4hour' => time() - 14400]); // 4 hours
$activeUsers4hour = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC)['active_users'];

// Added 4-hour traffic calculation
$time4hourStart = max(time() - 14400, $todayStart);
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT SUM(u) as upload, SUM(d) as download FROM user_usage WHERE t >= :time_4hour');
$stmt->execute([':time_4hour' => $time4hourStart]);
```

The backend now returns 4-hour data in the live statistics API response:

```json
{
  "active_users": {
    "5min": 125,
    "1hour": 456,
    "4hour": 789,
    "24hours": 1234
  },
  "traffic_periods": {
    "5min": {"upload": 1000, "download": 2000, "total": 3000},
    "1hour": {"upload": 15000, "download": 30000, "total": 45000},
    "4hour": {"upload": 60000, "download": 120000, "total": 180000},
    "monthly": {"upload": 500000, "download": 1000000, "total": 1500000}
  }
}
```

### 🔧 Technical Details

- **Database queries**: 4-hour calculations use a 14,400-second lookback (4 × 3600 seconds)
- **Boundary protection**: Traffic calculations respect today's start boundary to prevent including merged data from previous days
- **Caching compatibility**: All changes work seamlessly with the existing Redis caching infrastructure
- **Error handling**: Added proper fallback values for 4-hour statistics in error scenarios

### 🎯 Files Modified

- **Language files** (3): Added 4-hour labels and updated custom range translations
- **Backend** (1): Enhanced statistics calculation with 4-hour support
- **Templates** (2): Added 4-hour display elements and JavaScript handlers

The implementation follows existing code patterns and maintains full backward compatibility while adding the requested functionality exactly as specified in the requirements.

issue.title: Jellyfin 10.10.x (and 10.11.0-rc4) not splitting audio artists containing "feat." into multiple artists
issue.body:
### Description of the bug

On Jellyfin 10.10.x, when creating a music library, an artist tag containing "feat." is not split up anymore into multiple artists.

I tested in on 10.10.0, 10.11.0-rc4 and on 10.10.7 on Windows and 10.10.7 on Linux.

I just installed 10.9.11 for testing, and it works fine there. So, it seems to be a regression in 10.10x. I could not find it mentioned in the release notes, so I assume it is not a intended change.

### Reproduction steps

1. Create a music library
2. Add a directory containing mp3 files that have an ARTIST tag consisting of e.g. "Eminem feat. His Mother"
3. Finish the library creation
4. Login to Jellyfin and navigate to the created music library
5. Look which artists have been created in the database
6. You will see only "Eminem feat. His Mother" been created

### What is the current _bug_ behavior?

Only one artist called "Eminem feat. His Mother" has been created.

### What is the expected _correct_ behavior?

There should be two artists: "Eminem" and "His Mother".

10.10.0+

issue.title: [Enhancement] integrate global dict with flatjson
issue.body:
## Why I'm doing:

## What I'm doing:

Part of #60953

Support for Global Dictionary in FlatJSON-v2:
- Enable on-demand collection of the global dictionary for JSON paths.
- Enhance the metascan functionality to support dictionary collection for JSON fields.
- Rewrite JSON expressions, such as `get_json_string`, to utilize dictionary-based columns.
- Introduce a new function, `inspect_global_dict`, for debugging and testing purposes.

Limitation:
- The JSON data dictionary is not updated at the field level, making it challenging to manage individual fields within the dictionary.
- Consequently, if a table includes a JSON column, the dictionary becomes invalidated after any modification to the table, requiring recollection of the dictionary—even when the data change does not actually impact the dictionary.

- カレンダーとモバイルリストで一貫した祝日表示を実装
- シフトなしの表示を「祝日」から「シフトなし」に統一

💄 Improve weekend display in shift calendar components

土曜日と日曜日を視覚的に区別できるよう表示を改善
- 土曜日: 青色のテーマで表示
- 日曜日: 祝日と同様に赤色で表示
- カレンダーとモバイルリストの両方で一貫した表示

💄 ダークモード対応のシフトカレンダー土日表示改善

- 土曜日専用のスタイリング設定
- ダークモード対応の色彩設計
- 日曜日と祝日の色彩統一
- コードの可読性とパフォーマンス向上

♻️ Simplify shift day data handling to non-null type

WeeklyShiftListとShiftDayCardで、dayDataの型をDayData | nullから
DayDataに変更し、空のシフト配列を返すことで常にデータが存在する
状態にした。これにより不要なnullチェックを削除できた。

💄 Improve WeekNavigation responsive layout and UX

モバイル/デスクトップのレイアウトを改善し、ユーザビリティを向上:
- モバイル: 期間表示を中央に配置し、週移動ボタンとカレンダーボタンを最適化
- デスクトップ: 対称的なレイアウトで前週・来週ボタンを両端に配置
- touch-manipulation とホバーエフェクトでタッチデバイスの操作性を向上

💄 Improve WeekNavigation calendar button design

カレンダーボタンのスタイリングを改善。未使用変数の削除も実施。

💄 Improve WeekNavigation calendar functionality

カレンダーコンポーネントの機能性とデザインを改善：
- 外部クリック時の自動クローズ機能を追加
- date-fns/locale jaを使用した日本語対応
- captionLayout dropdown対応で年月選択を簡易化
- 今日ボタンのスタイルをghost variantに変更

💄 祝日表示の視認性を向上
- 祝日ラベルにバッジスタイルを適用し、視認性を改善
- ダークモード対応も含む

♻️ Refactor shift components to improve code reusability and maintainability

- ShiftBottomModal.tsxから共通コンポーネント関数を抽出・移動
- transformShiftsToStats関数をカスタムフックに移動し、コードの再利用性を向上
- 未使用インポートを削除し、コードベースを整理

🗃️ Add unique shift constraint and complete database schema

- Prismaマイグレーションを追加して重複シフト制約を実装
- スキーマに一意制約を追加（日付・部門・シフト種別の組み合わせ）
- データベース完全スキーマの初期マイグレーションを含む

✨ Implement duplicate shift detection and force override functionality

シフト作成APIに重複検出機能を実装
- 同一日付・部門・シフト種別の重複チェック
- forceフラグによる強制更新オプション
- 既存シフト情報を含む詳細エラーレスポンス
- Prisma unique constraint違反の適切な処理
- シードデータの改善（より現実的なシフト配置）

✨ Integrate shift preparation API with edit mode detection

シフト作成フローに重複チェックと編集モード検出機能を統合:

- 新規コンポーネント: DuplicateShiftDialog.tsx で重複時の対応選択肢を提供
- 統合API: /api/shifts/prepare で事前チェックと編集準備を実行
- クライアント: shiftApiClient.ts で統一的なAPI呼び出し管理
- UI改善: ShiftBottomModal.tsx で編集モード表示とワークフロー統合
- API文書: OpenAPI仕様にprepareエンドポイントを追加

既存シフト検出時は自動的に編集モードに移行し、
ユーザーフレンドリーな重複解決オプションを提供する

✨ Add direct edit functionality to shift management modal

- 未使用のcreateeDepartmentSectionインポートを削除
- Step1をスキップするhandleDirectEdit関数を実装
- クリック可能なcreateClickableDepartmentSectionを追加
- シフト準備APIと統合してシームレスな編集を実現
- UX向上のためエラー表示を追加
- シフト表示から直接Step2へアクセス可能に

ユーザビリティ向上のため、シフト作成フローのボタン表示を改善：
- 「戻る」を「キャンセル」に変更して意図を明確化
- ナビゲーション処理の統一化

ユーザーが操作結果を即座に確認できるようになった

✨ Add department-based instructor filtering

部門IDパラメータによるインストラクター絞り込み機能を実装
指定された部門の資格を持つインストラクターのみ表示可能
APIドキュメントも更新してパラメータ仕様を明記

✨ Improve instructor certification badge display

インストラクター一覧での資格認定バッジ表示を改善しました。
部門タイプに応じたバッジスタイルを適用し、具体的な資格略称を表示するようになりました。
また、不要な全体人数表示を削除し、表示を整理しました。

♻️ Extract certification badge to reusable component

資格バッジ表示を共通コンポーネント化して重複を排除
InstructorsPageとShiftBottomModalで同じバッジロジックを使用

✅ Add shift duplicate check mocking to tests

シフト作成時の重複チェック機能に対応するため、findUniqueメソッドのモック設定を追加。
成功メッセージの日本語化とエラーハンドリングの改善も含む。

issue.title: Chrome полностью заблокировал расширение
issue.body:
Google Chrome (Windows) убрал расширение runet-censorship-bypass из webstore и отказывается работать с расширением, даже если установить его вручную: ошибка "Manifest version 2 is deprecated, and support will be removed in 2024".
Есть ли какой-нибудь выход?

comment.body:
Всем привет! В силу того, что данное расширение все сложнее заставить работать (спасибо, Гугл), я набросал альтернативное расширение под названием "Менеджер PAC Прокси": [https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/pac-proxy-manager/jkdcbabhagklbkoidneelnhbhcliekak?authuser=0&hl=ru](https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/pac-proxy-manager/jkdcbabhagklbkoidneelnhbhcliekak?authuser=0&hl=ru)
Суть его та же (загружаешь любой PAC скрипт, указываешь свои прокси, также можно добавлять исключения по доменам), но ни в названии, ни в функционале нет привязки к обходу блокировок, что делает его более универсальным и устойчивым к блокировкам. В контексте обхода блокировок РФ, нужно сделать всего два шага:
1. Добавить любой PAC скрипт обхода блокировок, например Anticensority: [https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anticensority/generated-pac-scripts/master/anticensority.pac](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/anticensority/generated-pac-scripts/master/anticensority.pac)
2. Добавить свои прокси
3. Наслаждаться, что заблокированные сайты снова работают

Также стоит отметить, что это расширение гораздо более легковесно и требует всего 3 базовых пермишна. Оно не знает, на какие сайты вы заходите и к каким URL обращаетесь, и работает быстрее.

Если вам оно помогло, буду благодарен 5 звездам на странице Chrome Store 🙂 
Если нет, то открыт к обратной связи: [https://github.com/ilyachase/pac-proxy-manager-extension/issues/new](https://github.com/ilyachase/pac-proxy-manager-extension/issues/new)

Всем добра и свободного сёрфинга!
